FBIS4-48456 "drafr097_c_94008" FBIS-AFR-94-097 Daily Report 18 May 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Minister Notes Need for Improving Education Minister Notes Need for Improving Education MB1805182494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1400 GMT 18 May 94 MB1805182494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] The minister of education, Professor Sibusiso Bengu, says black people will remain an underclass in the economy unless his department intervenes decisively to improve their educational qualifications. With this in mind, he said he had initiated a series of processes to bring about the restructuring of the education system. Prof. Bhengu said the directors general and other managers in the old system would remain in charge of their departments until the new system was in place.
